
[1]pubescence

   PUBES'CENCE, n. [L. pubescens, pubesco, to shoot, to grow mossy or
   hairy.]

   1. The state of a youth who has arrived at puberty; or the state of
   puberty.

   2. In botany, hairiness; shagginess; the hairy or downy substance on
   plants.
